He told you to take care of yourself and not to exhaust yourself.

31
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,100
Is he downstairs?

32
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:12,300
He left after giving me this.

33
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:24,100
 Hello, the number you have dialed is powered off. 

34
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:26,100
What's the matter?

35
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:29,100
What's the matter?

36
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:32,500
I told my dad I wanted to take care of Lin Tuo in his house.

37
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,900
Doesn't your dad agree?

38
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:37,500
My dad wouldn't let me out or bring me the things if he doesn't agree.

39
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,800
He is not that kind of person.

40
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:44,500
He feels pity for Lin Tuo. This big box is filled with nutritional supplements.

41
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,400
He feels pity for Lin Tuo. This big box is filled with nutritional supplements.

42
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,900
A'Bao, come and help me put this inside.

43
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:53,700
You two go ahead with your things.

44
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,900
Go ahead.

45
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:40,700
Your dad doesn't agree you to come over, right?

46
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:45,700
If that's the case, he would not buy these things.

47
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,300
Then why doesn't he answer your call?

48
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,600
He's driving, so can't answer the call.

49
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:52,400
Don't overthink it.

50
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,400
Don't you know my dad?

51
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:58,200
He's afraid I couldn't take good care of you.

52
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,900
I still put all of you in trouble.

53
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:12,500
If I were the one who got sick, would you come and take care of me?

54
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:15,900
Would you come if your parents wouldn't agree?

55
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,900
Yes.

56
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,800
Then it's okay.

57
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:29,900
The water is here. Miss He Xindi, I have been waiting for you.

58
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:32,900
Thank you, Miss He Xindi.

59
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:38,100
What for? Are you serious?

60
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,900
Yes. What's the matter?

61
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,900
Don't you men like being taken care of?

62
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:50,800
What do you mean?

63
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,600
Cut the crap.

64
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,000
Tell me if Lin Tuo is going to be paralyzed or not.

65
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,200
If yes, someone has to take care of him.

66
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,100
How much does it cost to hire a free caretaker?

67
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:04,300
Now Xiao Que is there. You don't need to pay her or worry about her taking care of Xiao Tuo.

68
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,800
She is like a free caretaker now.

69
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,700
Well, He Xindi. Let me ask you.

70
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:12,500
First, is An Zhique Lin Tuo's girlfriend?

71
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:16,100
Second, does Lin Tuo treat An Zhique well?

72
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,700
Of course.

73
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:20,200
Everything's fine before he gets sick. What's the point?

74
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,900
If Lin Tuo doesn't treat Xiao Que well, could Xiao Que be with him?

75
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:25,300
- It's so different. 
 - Well...

76
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:30,100
You men are selfish. If it were you, could you do the same?

77
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:32,900
He Xindi, can you stop thinking this way?

78
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:36,700
Let me tell you, He Xindi. If you got sick,

79
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:41,600
I assure you I won't leave you. Absolutely. I can do it.

80
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:46,200
- I-I... 
 - Chen Guangpu, are you nuts?

81
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:48,300
Are you cursing me to be sick? You! What have I done to you?

82
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:52,200
- Why do you hate me so much? Are you nuts? 
 - Is this the point?

83
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:56,900
- What's wrong with you? Can't we talk properly? 
 - You're the one who's wrong. I don't want to talk to you properly

84
00:06:56,900 --> 00:07:00,000
- You just now... 
 - You just go home.

85
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,200
- Wait, where are you going? 
 - None of your business.

86
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,600
I...

87
00:07:06,856 --> 00:07:12,452
   

88
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:15,200
- Sorry for the long wait. 
 - It's okay.

89
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,300
You're An Zhique, right?

90
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,500
Yes, I just called.

91
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,300
I'm the leader of the caregiving team. You can call me Xiao Qin.

92
00:07:22,300 --> 00:07:24,600
You can call me Xiao Que.

93
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,300
Are you familiar with the situation here?

94
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:31,000
- Yes. 
 - We are not exclusively for ALS patients.

95
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:34,900
We also take in some patients who are paralyzed and some who cannot take care of themselves.

96
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:40,500
Our main job here is to provide them with nursing care and some rehabilitation treatments.

97
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:43,700
Actually, I don't know it very well.

98
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:50,000
I just want to learn and apply for the intern caregiver.

99
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:56,100
It's not an easy job, actually. I suggest you give it a try.

100
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,800
Do you have a patient at home?

101
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,500
Yes, my boyfriend has ALS.

102
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,300
Boyfriend?

103
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:07,000
Well, you are really remarkable.

104
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:11,300
Fill out this form first.

105
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,200
I will arrange it for you.

106
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,300
Okay, thank you.

107
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,700
Today we'll learn about nursing knowledge. 
    

108
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,400
Let's talk about food first.

109
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:28,800
The bedridden patients require a diet high in calories, protein and vitamins.

110
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,300
I'm coming.

111
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,900
Uncle.

112
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,400
Come on, be careful.

113
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,900
Sit down.

114
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:19,500
Uncle, please sit.

115
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,100
Okay.

116
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,200
- Uncle, have some water. 
 - I can do it myself.

117
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:43,550
I thought about everything when you broke up with Que,

118
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:46,800
except for this.

119
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,400
I didn't expect it either.

120
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Uncle, I didn't mean to keep it from you.

121
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:02,700
Breakup really hurts Xiao Que.

122
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:04,500
Xiao Tuo.

123
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:12,000
You know that Xiao Que's mom passed away early on, right?

124
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,100
I know.

125
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,500
It was cancer.

126
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:25,100
Xiao Que was only four years old when her mom passed away.

127
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:27,100
She knew nothing.

128
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:31,200
She even thought her mom had gone to work out of town.

129
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:39,200
I used to take taxis during the day and live in the hospital at night.

130
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,400
For three and a half years.

131
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:46,100
You may not believe this.

132
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:50,300
I took a shower once a month and I really smelled.

133
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:55,900
In the last year, I couldn't even drive the taxi anymore.

134
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:59,700
Because I fell asleep while waiting for the traffic signal,

135
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,700
I feared causing an accident.

136
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:08,300
I lost over 15 kg in those three and a half years.

137
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:12,600
Others might think I was the one who got sick.

138
00:11:15,300 --> 00:11:21,000
It was about both physical and mental exhaustion.

139
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,900
I felt lost and hopeless.

140
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:31,300
I am not superstitious.

141
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,800
But during that time, whenever I saw a temple, I would go and burn incense.

142
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:36,100
I would go kowtow and pray.

143
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:40,900
I wanted someone could help me to drive her mom's illness away.

144
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,200
I hoped someone to help me.

145
00:11:44,705 --> 00:11:46,419
But it was useless.

146
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,800
Her mom passed away anyway.

147
00:11:55,500 --> 00:12:01,000
All those years of carrying her mom to go around,

148
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,100
this arm of mine is now paralyzed.

149
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:07,440
You might not even know.

150
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:12,100
I can't even lift my arm. If I want to lift my arm...

151
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:21,500
That's why I never wanted to go to the hospital.

152
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:25,000
Because the smell of the hospital reminds me of those three and a half years.

153
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:29,600
I want to forget it, but I can't.

154
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:34,300
Now, once I close my eyes, those scenes come to me just like a movie.

155
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:43,900
So you don't want Xiao Que to be like this.

156
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,600
I don't.

157
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,900
I really don't.

158
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:52,000
It's a torture to live those days.

159
00:12:54,900 --> 00:13:00,500
Xiao Tuo, I'm not being selfish.

160
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:03,600
And I like you, you're like a son to me.

161
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,400
But I'm a dad.

162
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:10,900
Sometimes I wish I could just take over for Xiao Que.

163
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:15,000
I've suffered before, so it doesn't matter if I suffer a few more years.

164
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:19,400
But I really don't want my daughter to suffer too.

165
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,600
C-Can you understand me?

166
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,300
Yes.

167
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,900
If I have a choice,

168
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:38,600
the last person I want to be a burden to is Xiao Que.

169
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:45,600
My love for Xiao Que is not less than you.

170
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:51,400
I know.

171
00:13:53,900 --> 00:14:00,400
Actually, I came here today to beg you to let...

172
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:08,400
But I-I'm really struggling with this.

173
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:12,700
I don't want my daughter to suffer,

174
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:16,800
but I feel sorry for you if she leaves you.

175
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,000
To be honest,

176
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,700
when Xiao Que told me about your matter,

177
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,660
I tried to stop her,

178
00:14:29,350 --> 00:14:31,200
but failed.

179
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:37,800
I know my daughter well. She's just stubborn.

180
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,700
This might be fate.

181
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:48,400
When her mom got sick, I was told to give up,

182
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,000
even relatives told me so.

183
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:55,400
But I never give up.

184
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:59,700
As long as there is a glimmer of hope,

185
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:03,700
we have to go all out for it.

186
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:11,100
So, Xiao Tuo, strong will is what one should have.

187
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:15,100
An Zhique has the strong will.

188
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:17,300
I hope you do too.

189
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:20,800
The two of you need to pull together and move forward together.

190
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,600
Since you can't change it,

191
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:27,600
just face it.

192
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:35,100
I want to tell you. For the sake of my daughter

193
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:38,900
and her strong will to you,

194
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:41,200
you should stick with it,

195
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,600
okay?

196
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,700
Uncle, rest assured,

197
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,300
I will.

198
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:58,800
Good.

199
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:22,700
Excuse me. Clear the elevator.

200
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:25,000
He was fine just now, but what's wrong with him now?

201
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,000
Make way.

202
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:54,100
Hello, Xiao Ye. Where are you?

203
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,500
Xiao Y-Ye.

204
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,900
What's wrong?

205
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:35,700
Nothing. I just played...

206
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:38,300
- soccer before... 
 - You're still lying.

207
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,000
You're in a wheelchair and still lying to me.

208
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,600
Xiao Ye.

209
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,400
When did this happen?

210
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,100
Two months ago.

211
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:57,900
Mom and Dad know it, right?

212
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,300
Just keeping it from me

213
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:07,300
and treating me like a child. I don't deserve to know your affairs?

214
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,800
You don't tell me anything about the family anyway.

215
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:14,000
Mom and Dad treat me this way, and so do you.

216
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,800
- No, Xiao Ye. 
 - You did.

217
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:19,100
You said to stand by my side no matter what, and tell me to trust you!

218
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:23,600
But what now? Have you ever trusted me? Do you even consider me your brother?

219
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:27,300
- Xuai Ye, I don't want to affect you. 
 - Enough. You all are acting like this.

220
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:32,300
You'll do what you want, and never consider me. I am just superfluous.

221
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:36,800
If I hadn't come today, I didn't even know my brother is already disabled.

222
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:07,800
- Are you going to spend the night here? 
 - Not your business.

223
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:11,100
So whose business is it?

224
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,700
Your brother is sick now, so stop being willful.

225
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:18,500
Why didn't you tell me?

226
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,400
I just found out too.

227
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:24,500
Your brother didn't tell anyone. We just found it out.

228
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:28,500
He was diagnosed for over half a year.

229
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:32,700
He got slapped by your dad for you,

230
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,300
saved the money for you as living expenses,

231
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:40,300
and sent you to school with a smile. What else do you want from him?

232
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:44,800
I hate it when he's like this, carrying everything on his own like a savior.

233
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:48,000
Why didn't he tell us about his illness? Why?

234
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:50,800
Because he loves us.

235
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:55,000
If he could carry it himself until the end, he definitely wouldn't tell anyone.

236
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,300
But this disease will take years, so he can't carry it himself anymore.

237
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:03,000
It hurts him more when all of us know.

238
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:07,500
Because we have to watch him weaken, and none of us can save him.

239
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:13,400
You can't save him if you know everything.

240
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:21,700
Xiao Ye, your brother has at most five years left.

241
